Oh dear, didn't know that. *puke*. Ahem. Anyway... Veganism can be a good concept, however it tends to be much less realistic than vegetarianism and here's why... For one, human development relies heavily on calcium from milk and protein from eggs, etc. Many people would not be willing to give up their precious fatty foods even when confronted with such compelling evidence such as possible heart disease and cancer. Also, veganism requires much more work to maintain diet and nutrition. There are supplements and such out there, but let's face it, people are lazy in general. I can't even remember to take a daily vitamin, let alone figure out the supplements for all that I need in my diet which I would not be getting from milk and egg products. People would have to be pretty informed and educated on the subject of nutrition in order to eat healthily on that sort of diet, or else some might end up in a worse situation than if they had been eating tons of milk and cheese et cetera all their lives. Malnutrition is always a significant concern, and it tends to be pretty common in vegans and often even vegetarians. It's a heavy personal decision that has to be carefully considered... And most of the world does not seem ready for veganism. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003399><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/udashofmooo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dash Of Mooo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/Strobe.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/